## CHECK GROUP 2 — GenAiFunction Metadata

**2.1 — Required directory structure**
Each GenAiFunction MUST have this exact layout:
```
genAiFunctions/
  └── <FunctionName>/
      ├── <FunctionName>.genAiFunction-meta.xml
      ├── input/
      │   └── schema.json
      └── output/
          └── schema.json
```
- FAIL if `input/schema.json` is missing
- FAIL if `output/schema.json` is missing
- FAIL if the directory name does not match the file name (before `.genAiFunction-meta.xml`)

Fix: Create the missing directories and stub schema files.
```bash
mkdir -p genAiFunctions/Create_Account/input genAiFunctions/Create_Account/output
touch genAiFunctions/Create_Account/input/schema.json
touch genAiFunctions/Create_Account/output/schema.json
```
Minimum valid stub for each schema.json:
```json
{
  "unevaluatedProperties": false,
  "properties": {},
  "lightning:type": "lightning__objectType"
}
```

**2.2 — invocationTarget namespace**
- In source / scratch org context: `invocationTarget` MUST NOT include the namespace prefix (e.g., use `CreateAccountAction`, not `d26__CreateAccountAction`)
- In packaged / subscriber org context: `invocationTarget` MUST include the namespace prefix
- WARN if the target contains a namespace prefix but the file lives in an unpackaged source directory (e.g., `force-app/` or `force-app-accounts/`)

Fix: Remove the namespace prefix from `invocationTarget` when deploying source to a scratch org.
```xml
<!-- BEFORE (WARN — source deploy context) -->
<invocationTarget>d26__CreateAccountAction</invocationTarget>

<!-- AFTER (PASS — source deploy context) -->
<invocationTarget>CreateAccountAction</invocationTarget>
```
When building a package version or referencing from a subscriber org, the prefix is required:
```xml
<!-- Correct for packaged/subscriber context -->
<invocationTarget>d26__CreateAccountAction</invocationTarget>
```

**2.3 — invocationTargetType**
Must be `apex` for Apex-backed actions.
- FAIL if missing

Fix: Add the element immediately after `<invocationTarget>`.
```xml
<!-- BEFORE (FAIL) -->
<invocationTarget>CreateAccountAction</invocationTarget>

<!-- AFTER (PASS) -->
<invocationTarget>CreateAccountAction</invocationTarget>
<invocationTargetType>apex</invocationTargetType>
```

**2.4 — Required XML fields**
The following fields MUST be present in `.genAiFunction-meta.xml`:
- `<masterLabel>`
- `<description>`
- `<invocationTarget>`
- `<invocationTargetType>`
- WARN if `<progressIndicatorMessage>` is missing (best practice)

Fix: A complete, valid `.genAiFunction-meta.xml`:
```xml
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<GenAiFunction xmlns="http://soap.sforce.com/2006/04/metadata">
    <description>Creates a new Account record with Name and optional billing address fields</description>
    <invocationTarget>CreateAccountAction</invocationTarget>
    <invocationTargetType>apex</invocationTargetType>
    <isConfirmationRequired>false</isConfirmationRequired>
    <isIncludeInProgressIndicator>true</isIncludeInProgressIndicator>
    <masterLabel>Create Account</masterLabel>
    <progressIndicatorMessage>Creating Account...</progressIndicatorMessage>
</GenAiFunction>
```

**2.5 — Schema uses lightning__ standard types**
Input and output `schema.json` files MUST use `lightning__` standard types, NOT `@apexClassType`.
Valid types: `lightning__textType`, `lightning__booleanType`, `lightning__numberType`, `lightning__objectType`, `lightning__listType`
- FAIL if `@apexClassType` appears in any schema.json
- FAIL if `lightning:type` is missing from any property

Fix: Replace `@apexClassType` references with the appropriate `lightning__` type.
```json
// BEFORE (FAIL)
{
  "properties": {
    "fieldValuesJson": { "type": "@apexClassType" }
  }
}

// AFTER (PASS)
{
  "properties": {
    "fieldValuesJson": {
      "title": "Field Values (JSON)",
      "description": "JSON string of field API names and values",
      "lightning:type": "lightning__textType",
      "lightning:isPII": false,
      "copilotAction:isUserInput": false
    }
  }
}
```

**2.6 — schema.json root object type**
Both input and output schema.json MUST have `"lightning:type": "lightning__objectType"` at the root level.
- FAIL if missing

Fix: Add `"lightning:type": "lightning__objectType"` as a top-level key in the schema.
```json
// BEFORE (FAIL)
{
  "unevaluatedProperties": false,
  "properties": { ... }
}

// AFTER (PASS)
{
  "unevaluatedProperties": false,
  "properties": { ... },
  "lightning:type": "lightning__objectType"
}
```

**2.7 — unevaluatedProperties**
Both schema.json files SHOULD include `"unevaluatedProperties": false`.
- WARN if missing

Fix: Add `"unevaluatedProperties": false` as a top-level key.
```json
{
  "unevaluatedProperties": false,
  "properties": { ... },
  "lightning:type": "lightning__objectType"
}
```

**2.8 — Required input fields marked correctly**
If the matching Apex `@InvocableVariable` has `required=true`, the input schema.json MUST include that field name in the `"required"` array.
- FAIL if a required Apex variable is not listed in schema `"required"`

Fix: Add a `"required"` array at the root of input/schema.json listing every field where the Apex variable has `required=true`.
```apex
// Apex
@InvocableVariable(label='Field Values (JSON)' required=true)
global String fieldValuesJson;
```
```json
// input/schema.json — AFTER (PASS)
{
  "required": ["fieldValuesJson"],
  "unevaluatedProperties": false,
  "properties": {
    "fieldValuesJson": { "lightning:type": "lightning__textType" }
  },
  "lightning:type": "lightning__objectType"
}
```

**2.9 — No list types in schema when used by Agent Script**
If this GenAiFunction will be consumed by an Agent Script action (i.e., has a matching `source:` reference), the output schema MUST NOT contain `lightning__listType` properties.
- FAIL if `lightning__listType` appears in output schema and a corresponding Agent Script `source:` reference exists

Fix: Remove the `lightning__listType` property from `output/schema.json`. The Apex method can still return that data — just don't declare it in the schema.
```json
// BEFORE (FAIL)
{
  "properties": {
    "fieldsJson":          { "lightning:type": "lightning__textType" },
    "requiredFieldNames":  { "lightning:type": "lightning__listType" }
  }
}

// AFTER (PASS)
{
  "properties": {
    "fieldsJson":    { "lightning:type": "lightning__textType" },
    "isSuccess":     { "lightning:type": "lightning__booleanType" },
    "errorMessage":  { "lightning:type": "lightning__textType" }
  }
}
```

**2.10 — Property names match Apex @InvocableVariable names exactly**
Every property key in input and output `schema.json` MUST match the exact field name (case-sensitive) declared with `@InvocableVariable` in the Apex class.
- FAIL if a mismatch is detected between schema property names and Apex field names

Fix: Copy the exact field name from the Apex `@InvocableVariable` declaration into the schema property key — including camelCase.
```apex
// Apex field name
@InvocableVariable global String fieldValuesJson;
```
```json
// BEFORE (FAIL) — wrong name
{ "properties": { "fieldValues": { ... } } }

// AFTER (PASS) — exact match
{ "properties": { "fieldValuesJson": { ... } } }
```

