## CHECK GROUP 3 — Agent Script (.agent files)

**3.1 — source + target both declared for packaged actions**
Any action referencing a packaged (namespaced) GenAiFunction MUST declare both:
- `source: "<namespace>__<FunctionApiName>"` — must match the GenAiFunction's full API name
- `target: "apex://<namespace>__<ApexClassName>"` — must match the Apex class with namespace
- FAIL if `source` is missing when action references a packaged GenAiFunction
- FAIL if `target` is missing

Fix: Add both `source` and `target` to the action declaration.
```yaml
# BEFORE (FAIL) — missing source and target
actions:
    Create_Account:
        description: "Creates a new Account"
        label: "Create Account"

# AFTER (PASS)
actions:
    Create_Account:
        description: "Creates a new Account"
        label: "Create Account"
        source: "d26__Create_Account"
        target: "apex://d26__CreateAccountAction"
        inputs:
            "fieldValuesJson": string
                description: "JSON string of field values"
                label: "Field Values (JSON)"
        outputs:
            "recordId": string
                description: "ID of the created Account"
                label: "Record Id"
            "isSuccess": boolean
                description: "Whether creation succeeded"
                label: "Success"
            "errorMessage": string
                description: "Error message if failed"
                label: "Error Message"
```

**3.2 — Agent Script outputs match GenAiFunction output schema exactly**
When `source` is present, the `outputs:` block in the Agent Script action MUST declare exactly the same property names as the GenAiFunction `output/schema.json`. No extras, no omissions.
- FAIL if a GenAiFunction output property is missing from the Agent Script outputs block
- FAIL if the Agent Script declares an output not present in the GenAiFunction schema

Fix: Open the GenAiFunction `output/schema.json` and mirror every property key in the Agent Script `outputs:` block. Remove any Agent Script outputs not in the schema, and add any schema properties missing from Agent Script.
```json
// output/schema.json has: recordId, recordName, recordLink, isSuccess, errorMessage
```
```yaml
# BEFORE (FAIL) — recordName and recordLink missing, extra field present
outputs:
    "recordId": string
    "isSuccess": boolean
    "someExtraField": string   # not in schema

# AFTER (PASS) — exact match
outputs:
    "recordId": string
        description: "ID of the created record"
        label: "Record Id"
    "recordName": string
        description: "Name of the created record"
        label: "Record Name"
    "recordLink": string
        description: "Rich text hyperlink to the record"
        label: "Record Link"
    "isSuccess": boolean
        description: "Whether creation succeeded"
        label: "Success"
    "errorMessage": string
        description: "Error message if failed"
        label: "Error Message"
```

**3.3 — No list types in Agent Script outputs**
Agent Script does NOT support `list of string`, `list of number`, or any array type.
- FAIL if any output declares `list of <type>`

Fix: Remove list-type outputs entirely from the Agent Script `outputs:` block. Also remove the corresponding property from the GenAiFunction `output/schema.json` (see check 2.9). Serialize list data as a JSON string in Apex and declare it as `string` instead.
```yaml
# BEFORE (FAIL)
outputs:
    "requiredFieldNames": list of string

# AFTER (PASS) — serialize to JSON string in Apex, expose as string
outputs:
    "requiredFieldNamesJson": string
        description: "JSON array of required field names"
        label: "Required Field Names (JSON)"
```

**3.4 — Supported Agent Script types only**
Valid Agent Script types: `string`, `number`, `boolean`, `object`, `currency`, `date`, `datetime`, `time`, `timestamp`, `id`, `integer`, `long`
- FAIL if any input or output uses an unsupported type

Fix: Replace unsupported types with their nearest valid equivalent.
```yaml
# BEFORE (FAIL)
outputs:
    "count": int          # not valid
    "tags": array         # not valid

# AFTER (PASS)
outputs:
    "count": integer
    "tags": string        # serialize array as JSON string
```

**3.5 — source API name matches full namespaced GenAiFunction name**
The `source:` value must equal `<namespace>__<FunctionDeveloperName>` where `FunctionDeveloperName` matches the GenAiFunction directory name.
- FAIL if source value does not match the GenAiFunction developer name (with namespace)

Fix: The `source` value must be `<namespace>__` + the exact GenAiFunction directory name.
```
# GenAiFunction directory: genAiFunctions/Create_Account/
# Namespace: d26

# BEFORE (FAIL)
source: "d26__CreateAccount"      # wrong — missing underscore separator

# AFTER (PASS)
source: "d26__Create_Account"     # matches directory name exactly
```

**3.6 — Agent Script is NOT packaged**
`AiAuthoringBundle` / `.agent` files are not packageable in 2GP. They must be distributed via an LWC component, documentation, or the AppExchange listing.
- WARN if `.agent` files are found inside a `packageDirectory` path in `sfdx-project.json`

Fix: Move the Agent Script source into an LWC JavaScript file as a string constant and provide a copy-to-clipboard UI. Remove any `.agent` / `AiAuthoringBundle` entries from `package.xml`.
```javascript
// lwc/agentScriptSetup/agentScriptsData.js
const CREATE_ACCOUNT_AGENT = `
system:
    instructions: |
        You help users create Account records in Salesforce.
...
`;
export { CREATE_ACCOUNT_AGENT };
```
Remove from `package.xml`:
```xml
<!-- REMOVE THIS BLOCK -->
<types>
    <members>MyAgent</members>
    <name>AiAuthoringBundle</name>
</types>
```

