## CHECK GROUP 4 — GenAiPlugin (optional but validated if present)

**4.1 — GenAiPlugin references functions by API name without namespace**
`<genAiFunctionName>` inside a GenAiPlugin must use the bare developer name (no namespace prefix).
- FAIL if a namespace prefix appears in `<genAiFunctionName>`

Fix: Remove the namespace prefix from every `<genAiFunctionName>` in the plugin file.
```xml
<!-- BEFORE (FAIL) -->
<genAiFunctions>
    <genAiFunctionName>d26__Create_Account</genAiFunctionName>
</genAiFunctions>

<!-- AFTER (PASS) -->
<genAiFunctions>
    <genAiFunctionName>Create_Account</genAiFunctionName>
</genAiFunctions>
```

**4.2 — Referenced functions exist**
Every `<genAiFunctionName>` listed in the plugin must correspond to a GenAiFunction directory in the project.
- FAIL if a referenced function name has no matching GenAiFunction directory

Fix: Either create the missing GenAiFunction directory (see check 2.1 for structure), or remove the stale reference from the plugin.
```xml
<!-- Remove this line if Create_Account directory does not exist -->
<genAiFunctionName>Create_Account</genAiFunctionName>
```

