## CHECK GROUP 5 — Packaging Configuration

**5.1 — sfdx-project.json namespace**
A namespace must be set at the project level in `sfdx-project.json`.
- WARN if `"namespace"` is absent or empty

Fix: Add the `"namespace"` key to the root of `sfdx-project.json`. The value must match the namespace registered in your Dev Hub org.
```json
// BEFORE (WARN)
{
  "packageDirectories": [ ... ],
  "name": "My Package"
}

// AFTER (PASS)
{
  "packageDirectories": [ ... ],
  "name": "My Package",
  "namespace": "d26",
  "sfdcLoginUrl": "https://login.salesforce.com",
  "sourceApiVersion": "66.0"
}
```

**5.2 — packageMetadataAccess for PromptTemplate**
If the project includes PromptTemplate metadata, `sfdx-project.json` must include `"EinsteinGPTPromptTemplateManager"` in `packageMetadataAccess`.
- WARN if PromptTemplates exist but `packageMetadataAccess` does not include `EinsteinGPTPromptTemplateManager`

Fix: Add `packageMetadataAccess` to the relevant `packageDirectories` entry.
```json
// AFTER (PASS)
{
  "packageDirectories": [
    {
      "path": "force-app",
      "package": "My Package",
      "versionNumber": "0.1.0.NEXT",
      "packageMetadataAccess": [
        "EinsteinGPTPromptTemplateManager"
      ]
    }
  ]
}
```

**5.3 — Extension packages declare dependencies**
If multiple `packageDirectories` exist, any package that relies on types from another package MUST declare a `dependencies` entry.
- WARN if a second packageDirectory is present and has no `dependencies` declared

Fix: Add a `dependencies` array to the extension package's directory entry referencing the base package.
```json
// BEFORE (WARN)
{
  "path": "force-app-accounts",
  "package": "Agentforce Account Manager",
  "versionNumber": "0.1.0.NEXT"
}

// AFTER (PASS)
{
  "path": "force-app-accounts",
  "package": "Agentforce Account Manager",
  "versionNumber": "0.1.0.NEXT",
  "dependencies": [
    {
      "package": "Agentforce Opportunity Manager",
      "versionNumber": "0.1.0.LATEST"
    }
  ]
}
```

**5.4 — No AiAuthoringBundle in package manifest**
`package.xml` or `package-*.xml` manifests MUST NOT include `<name>AiAuthoringBundle</name>`.
- FAIL if present

Fix: Remove the entire `<types>` block for `AiAuthoringBundle` from the manifest.
```xml
<!-- REMOVE THIS BLOCK (FAIL) -->
<types>
    <members>MyAgent</members>
    <name>AiAuthoringBundle</name>
</types>
```

