## Validation Output Format

Report findings in this structure:

```
AGENTFORCE AGENT VALIDATION REPORT
===================================

[FAIL] 2.2 — invocationTarget namespace
  File: force-app/main/default/genAiFunctions/Create_Account/Create_Account.genAiFunction-meta.xml
  Issue: invocationTarget 'd26__CreateAccountAction' contains namespace prefix — remove for source deploy

[WARN] 1.4 — No unhandled exceptions surfaced
  File: force-app/main/default/classes/CreateAccountAction.cls:45
  Issue: @InvocableMethod body has no DmlException catch block

[PASS] 1.1 — Global access modifier
  File: force-app/main/default/classes/CreateAccountAction.cls

...

SCORECARD
---------
FAIL : 2
WARN : 3
PASS : 18
Total checks run: 23

Priority fixes:
1. [FAIL items listed with file + line]
```

Always list FAILs first, then WARNs, then PASSes. If a check cannot be evaluated (e.g., no Agent Script files present), mark it as SKIP with a reason.
